        <h1>LeetCode 2264: Largest 3-Same-Digit Number in String (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong> You are given a string num representing a large integer. Return the largest
                good integer as a string, which is a substring of num consisting of three identical digits. If no such
                substring exists, return an empty string.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> <br>
                Input: num = "6777133339" <br>
                Output: "777" <br>
                Explanation: There are two distinct good integers: "777" and "333". The largest among them is "777".
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    string largestGoodInteger(string num) {
        string res = "";
        for (int i = 0; i + 2 &lt; num.size(); ++i) {
            if (num[i] == num[i+1] &amp;&amp; num[i] == num[i+2]) {
                string curr = num.substr(i, 3);
                if (curr &gt; res) res = curr;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};</code></pre>
